<TITLE> Govt to print textbooks by Oct every year: official </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 2 (bdnews24.com)The education ministry has decided to complete the printing of textbooks for classes five to ten within October every year to avert a textbook crisis, a top official said. "Arrangements will be made so that apart from Dhaka, publishers at others districts can also participate in the bidding process," education secretary Syed Ataur Rahman told bdnews24.com. "Qualified bidders at the district level would be eligible for printing books," he said Thursday after ministry meeting. He warned of action against those who are involved in creating irregularities and said already 18 institutions had been blacklisted. On distributing free books at primary schools, he said, "We have sent a letter to the finance ministry asking for allocation of nearly Tk 300 crore. If sanctioned, books would be distributed through NCTB." The caretaker government had decided to distribute free books from 2010 at a cost of Tk 283 crore, he added Every year, crises of books at the secondary and below secondary level creep up, making books unavailable even at the double the price, professor Akteruzzaman, the chief of national expert committee, formed on Mar 9, said at a view-exchange meeting Tuesday. National Curriculum and Textboard Board chairman professor Khan Habibur Rahman told bdnews24.com Thursday that the plan for distribution of free books would need the prime minister's approval. "The process for procurement of paper is underway .Printing of books is also on the way," he added He said a NCTB delegation would assess the feasibility of printing books at the districts. 
